Nehemiah Group – Polo Shirt Base Design Plan (Right Sleeve Red Variant)
├─ Concept Goal: Achieve a clean white–red combination with a red right sleeve and a natural red-to-white gradient flow before adding logo or text.
│
├─ All View – Red-to-White Gradient Flow
│ ├─ Body: Soft, natural diagonal gradient transitioning from red (right shoulder and upper chest) fading gently into white (left torso and waist).
│ ├─ Collar: Black with thin red tipping (1 mm) along outer edge
│ ├─ Sleeves:
│ │ ├─ Left sleeve – solid white (keeps visual balance and cleanliness)
│ │ └─ Right sleeve – solid red (bold accent that anchors the gradient flow)
│ ├─ Accent: Gradient transition is smooth and seamless, visually connecting the red sleeve into the shirt body
│ ├─ Back View (Base Only): Mostly white with right sleeve red for continuity
│ ├─ Tone: Fresh • Dynamic • Balanced • Executive-sporty • Confident
│ └─ Mood: Forward momentum • Corporate energy • Modern precision • Motivational presence

Nehemiah Group – Polo Shirt Design Plan (Right Sleeve Red Variant + Hexagon Motif)
├─ Concept Goal: Layer a symbolic motif (hexagon + motion lines) onto the red–white–black base to represent engineering precision, unity, and forward acceleration.
│
├─ All Views – Gradient + Motif Integration
│ ├─ Body:
│ │ ├─ Keep the soft diagonal gradient (red → white, right to left).
│ │ ├─ Overlay faint hexagon outlines (2–3 large semi-transparent shapes) near upper right chest to midsection, aligned with the gradient direction.
│ │ ├─ Hexagon edges slightly blurred or translucent, in light grey or muted red, to blend naturally with the gradient.
│ │ └─ Represents Nehemiah’s engineering foundation and structural strength.
│ ├─ Dynamic Lines:
│ │ ├─ Add three thin angled red lines emerging subtly from the bottom right torso, sweeping diagonally upward to the left.
│ │ ├─ Lines should fade gradually, matching gradient tone.
│ │ └─ Symbolize Rejuvenate • Rebuild • Accelerate.
│ ├─ Shoulder Highlight: Optional single thin red line across the right shoulder connecting sleeve to chest — acts as visual flow link.
│ ├─ Collar: Keep matte black with red tipping (1 mm).
│ ├─ Sleeves:
│ │ ├─ Left – plain white
│ │ └─ Right – solid red (serves as color anchor for motif flow).
│ ├─ Balance: Ensure motifs don’t overpower gradient
│ ├─ Back View:
│ │ ├─ Faint continuation of hexagon pattern near the upper right shoulder blade, echoing front motif.
│ │ └─ Keep lower back plain white for minimalist contrast.
│ ├─ Tone: Futuristic • Technical • Elegant • Symbolic
│ └─ Mood: Precision • Momentum • Innovation • Strength in unity


